name: Twan Fenten
summary: Als afgestudeerde bachelorstudent Sociale Geografie ben ik breed geïnteresseerd in ruimtelijk-maatschappelijke vraagstukken. Tijdens mijn bachelor heb ik mij gespecialiseerd in Duurzame Ontwikkeling, een werkveld waar ik zeer gepassioneerd over ben. Aan de andere kant ligt mijn interesse in de communicatie. Als commissaris Extern bij V.U.G.S. heb ik mij bezig gehouden met acquisitie en fondsenwerving. Deze rol als contactpersoon tussen een vereniging en het bedrijfsleven gaf mij veel energie; ik hoop dat ik een dergelijke rol in de toekomst kan blijven beoefenen. In september 2021 ben ik begonnen aan de MSc Sustainable Development aan de Universiteit Utrecht om mijn kennis over duurzame ontwikkeling te vergroten. Naast mijn master ben ik werkzaam bij Grand Hotel Karel V als portier en ben ik verantwoordelijk voor het opstarten van een recruitment-project omtrent studentenwerving voor verscheidene parttime functies.

name: Stan Majoor
summary:
dr. Stan Majoor (1977) is Professor (Lector) Coordination of Urban Issues at the Amsterdam University of Applied Sciences (Hogeschool van Amsterdam). He is also the scientific director of the Centre of Expertise Urban Governance and Social Innovation​. Previously he worked as Programme Director, Assistant Professor, Post-doc and Junior Researcher at the Faculty of Social and Behavioural Sciences, University of Amsterdam, research center AISSR (Amsterdam Institute for Social Science Research).
His research interests are in governance puzzles regarding complex urban issues on the crossroads of spatial, social and economic domains. 

Between 2008 and 2012 he was Program Director of the Bachelor in Human Geography and Planning at the Department of Geography, Planning and International Development Studies and on the board of the College of Social Sciences of the University of Amsterdam.

Since 2001 he holds a Master degree in Urban and Regional Planning, and in Politics and Public Management from the Universiteit van Amsterdam. In 2008 he defended his PhD thesis on three large-scale urban development projects, Zuidas in Amsterdam, Ørestad in Copenhagen and Forum in Barcelona and their ambition for 'new urbanity'​. From June 2007 till August 2008 he was Visiting Assistant Professor at the Centre of Urban Planning and Environmental Management (CUPEM) of the University of Hong Kong. He has also had extended research stays in Copenhagen (Denmark), Barcelona (Spain) and Melbourne (Australia).
In 2009-2010 and from 2011 till 2019 he was holding the "Chair Leerhuis" at the Project Management Bureau of the municipality of Amsterdam. From 2013 till 2015 he was the is editor-in-chief of Rooilijn, a popular-scientific journal on policy making and urban and regional planning.

name: Adriaan de Klerk
summary: My background in urban planning has taught me a lot about spatial processes and the multidisciplinary nature of planning. In addition, I have always had a passion for programming and building websites. My knowledge and experience of multiple disciplines means that I can be a connector between the technical and human aspects of IT. In the future I would like to expand my knowledge in the field of programming, testing and operating applications.
